  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="KT346-kilavi">tōḻi kiḻattiyai iravukkuṟi nayappak kūṟiyatu. </p>


        <p xml:lang="en">Spoken [to inform HIM] that SHE would grant night
          trysts, by the confidante. </p>
      </div>

      <div rend="parallel">
        <lg xml:id="KT346">
          <l> nākupiṭi nayanta muḷaikkōṭ ṭiḷaṅkaḷiṟu</l>
          <l> kuṉṟa naṇṇik kuṟava rārppa</l>
          <l> maṉṟam pōḻu nāṭaṉ ṟōḻi</l>
          <l> cuṉaippūṅ kuvaḷait toṭalai tantun</l>
          <l> tiṉaippuṉa maruṅkiṟ paṭukiḷi yōppiyuṅ</l>
          <l> kālai vantu mālaip poḻuti</l>
          <l> ṉallaka nayantutā ṉuyaṅkic</l>
          <l> collavu mākā taḵki yōṉē.</l>


        </lg>

        <lg xml:lang="en">
          <l>The man from a land, friend,</l>
          <l rend="indent">where a young elephant bull with sprouting<note place="foot"> <term xml:lang="ta">  muḷai kōṭu </term> might also intend a comparison: "tusks [like] sprouts", i.e. still very small.    </note>  tusks,</l>
          <l rend="indent">who longed for the young female, [usually] staying in the hills<note place="foot"> What is the function of <term xml:lang="ta"> kuṉṟa naṇṇi </term> here? The elephant's place is the hills, but in search of his female he comes down into the village and gives people a fright – just like HE will upset HER people if she does not give in to him? </note> </l>
          <l rend="indent">crosses the village common, so that the hill people shout,</l>
          <l>giving a waterlily garland of flowers from the mountain pool</l>
          <l>and scaring away the parakeets falling into<note place="foot"> What is meant by <term xml:lang="ta"> maruṅkiṉ </term> ? Just a pronounced loc. suff.? </note>  the millet field</l>
          <l>having come in the morning, at evening time</l>
          <l>he longed in [his] good mind, became weak himself</l>
          <l>[and] even speaking was impossible<note place="foot">Here <hi rend="italic">ākātu</hi> has to be read as the main predicate and an early occurrence of <hi rend="italic">ākutal</hi> in the sense of <q>to be possible.</q></note> to him who was dejected.</l>


        </lg>
      </div>
